    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="1736"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1736">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 718.1915/211.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President of Costa Rica</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">President</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San José</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 13, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Costa Rica and my Government cordially applaud the award rendered by the
                    illustrious Chief Justice, and once more has the good fortune of settling its
                    boundary disputes through a decision dictated by the high sense of justice of
                    your great nation. Will your excellency please accept the expression of our
                    gratitude.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alfredo Gonzalez</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
